Have you ever dreamed of buying a spacious vintage home that you could put your own personal touches on? Then this may be the perfect opportunity for you! Built in 1929 and remodeled in the 1930s, 17921 Elaine Avenue has 3 bedrooms and 1 bathrooms with more than 1800 sq. ft. of living space and it sits on a large lot on a quiet residential street in the heart of Artesia. From the covered front porch, there are dual entries to the home, creating an opportunity for carving out separate living areas. One entry door leads to a large living room with a barrel ceiling, decorative fireplace and an oversized arched window overlooking the front yard. Attached to the living room and accessed via an archway is a graciously sized formal dining room with a tray ceiling. The other entry from the porch leads to a parlor and then a breakfast room with corner cabinets and the kitchen beyond. Off the galley kitchen is a large service area with laundry hookups and an exterior door leading to the yard. All three generously sized bedrooms have hardwood floors. The hall bathroom has period fixtures and tile along with built-in cabinetry. A finished attic area, accessed via stairway, is perfect for a home office, craft room, or perhaps a fourth bedroom. Out back, youll find a huge backyard with multiple trees and access to the detached 2 car garage and an additional storage / work room.
